name: Bulbasaur
description: Bulbasaur. It bears the seed of a plant on its back from birth. The seed slowly develops. Researchers are unsure whether to classify Bulbasaur as a plant or animal. Bulbasaur are extremely calm and very difficult to capture in the wild.

name: Ivysaur
description: The Seed Pokémon, Ivysaur, Bulbasaur's evolved form. The bulb on its back absorbs nourishment and blooms into a large flower.

name: Venusaur
description: Venusaur, the final form of the Bulbasaur evolution. This Seed Pokémon soaks up the sun's rays as a source of energy.

name: Charmander
description: Charmander. A flame burns on the tip of its tail from birth. It is said that a Charmander dies if its flame ever goes out.

name: Charmeleon
description: Charmeleon, the Flame Pokémon. It has razor-sharp claws and its tail is exceptionally strong.

name: Charizard
description: Charizard, the Flame Pokémon. Charizard's powerful flame can melt absolutely anything.

name: Squirtle
description: Squirtle. This Tiny Turtle Pokémon draws its long neck into its shell to launch incredible water attacks with amazing range and accuracy. The blasts can be quite powerful.

name: Wartortle
description: Wartortle, the Turtle Pokémon. The evolved form of Squirtle. Its long furry tail is a symbol of its age and wisdom.

name: Blastoise
description: Blastoise, the Shellfish Pokémon. The evolved form of Wartortle. Blastoise's strength lies in its power, rather than its speed. Its shell is like armor and attacks from the hydro cannons on its back are virtually unstoppable.

name: Caterpie
description: Caterpie, the Worm Pokémon. Caterpie uses the suction cups on its feet to climb trees and feed on its favorite leaves.

name: Metapod
description: Metapod, Caterpie's next stage. It has encased its body in a hard shell. This specimen reached this stage faster than any previously discovered Pokémon of this variety.

name: Butterfree
description: Butterfree. One week after Caterpie evolves into Metapod, it again evolves into Butterfree.

name: Weedle
description: Weedle. The stinger on this Pokémon's head guarantees that any attacker will get the point right where it hurts.

name: Kakuna
description: Kakuna, a transitional stage between Weedle and Beedrill. Kakunas remain inactive until they evolve into deadly Beedrills and hatch.

name: Beedrill
description: Beedrill. This Pokémon is an evolved form of Weedle, following its Kakuna stage. Its sting is highly poisonous.

name: Pidgey
description: Pidgey is a Flying Pokémon. Among all the Flying Pokémon, it is the gentlest and easiest to capture. A perfect target for the beginning Pokémon Trainer to test his Pokémon's skills.

name: Pidgeotto
description: Pidgeotto, an evolved form of the Pidgey. It is armed with sharp claws and dives from the sky to capture its prey. Unlike the more gentle Pidgey, Pidgeotto can be dangerous. Approach with extreme caution.

name: Pidgeot
description: Pidgeot, the Bird Pokémon. The evolved form of Pidgeotto. It can fly at twice the speed of sound at an altitude of nearly one mile.

name: Rattata
description: A Forest Pokémon, Rattata. It likes cheese, nuts, fruits, and berries. It also comes out into open fields to steal food from stupid travelers.

name: Raticate
description: Raticate, Rattata's evolved form . The Mouse Pokémon. When they band together, they steal food from people's homes.

name: Spearow
description: Unlike Pidgey, Spearow has a terrible attitude. It is very wild and will sometimes attack other Pokémon and humans.

name: Fearow
description: Fearow, the Beak Pokémon. The evolved form of Spearow. Its large, powerful wings allow it to fly for an entire day. The crushing power of its beak is tremendous.

name: Ekans
description: Ekans is a purple, serpentine Pokémon. Its eyes, underbelly, the thick stripe around its neck, and rattle are yellow. Ekans has three pairs of black lines encircling its body, as well as another line that connects each slitted eye and curves toward its nose. Its large mouth has a round, pink tongue and no visible teeth. While painful, a newborn Ekans's bite is not venomous. This Pokémon grows longer with age.

name: Arbok
description: Arbok is capable of crushing opponents by coiling its body around them and squeezing them tightly. It can even flatten steel oil drums. If it encounters an enemy, it raises its head, mimics and stuns the opponent using the frightening pattern on its body, and makes eerie sounds by expelling air from its mouth.

name: Pikachu
description: Pikachu, the Mouse Pokémon. It can generate electric attacks from the electric pouches located in both of its cheeks.

name: Raichu
description: Raichu, a Mouse Pokémon of the Electric element. Raichu is the evolved form of Pikachu. It can shock with more than 100,000 volts, enough to render a Dragonite unconscious.

name: Sandshrew
description: Sandshrew, the Mouse Pokémon. Sandshrew hates moisture and lives in holes it digs in dry places. It protects itself by curling into a ball.

name: Sandslash
description: Sandslash, the Mouse Pokémon. The evolved form of Sandshrew. It attacks opponents with the quills on its back.

name: Nidoran-f
description: Nidoran♀. Its poison pin is quite powerful for its size, but its horn is smaller than a male's.

name: Nidorina
description: Nidorina, the Poison Pin Pokémon. The evolved form of the female Nidoran. It emits supersonic waves from its mouth to confuse its enemies.

name: Nidoqueen
description: Nidoqueen, the Drill Pokémon. Nidoqueen has thick skin covering its entire body, protecting it from whatever techniques are used against it.

name: Nidoran-m
description: Nidoran♂. Its horn is larger than the female's and its Horn Attack is quite powerful.

name: Nidorino
description: Nidorino, the Poison Pin Pokémon. The evolved form of the male Nidoran. Its highly developed horn is extremely powerful.

name: Nidoking
description: Nidoking, the Drill Pokémon. Nidoking swings its large tail about to create distance, then charges in with the full force of its body behind it.

name: Clefairy
description: Clefairy. This impish Pokémon is friendly and peaceful. It is believed to live inside Mt. Moon, although very few have ever been seen by humans.

name: Clefable
description: Clefable, an advanced form of Clefairy. These unique creatures are among the rarest Pokémon in the world.

name: Vulpix
description: Vulpix, a Fox Pokémon. Its six tails are extremely beautiful. As it evolves, it grows even more tails. Vulpix uses powerful flame attacks.

name: Ninetales
description: Ninetales, the Fox Pokémon, is the evolved form of the Fire Pokémon Vulpix.

name: Jigglypuff
description: Jigglypuff, a Balloon Pokémon. It has large friendly eyes and it sings a pleasant song.

name: Wigglytuff
description: Wigglytuff resembles a pink blob with stubby arms and legs. There is a fluffy, curled tuft of fur on its head, and it has long, rabbit-like ears and large, blue eyes. A layer of tears covers its eyes, quickly washing away any debris. It is covered in pink fur with a white underbelly and ear tips. This fine layer of fur is so soft that those who touch it, including other Wigglytuff, will not want to stop. Its body is soft and rubbery, allowing it to inflate by inhaling.

name: Zubat
description: Zubat, blind Pokémon with supersonic powers. Zubat live in caves and hate to fly outside in daylight.

name: Golbat
description: Golbat. Attacking with its sharp fangs, this Pokémon can drain three hundred cubic centimeters of blood per bite.

name: Oddish
description: Oddish. This Pokémon is typically found roaming the forest, scattering pollen as it walks around.

name: Gloom
description: Gloom, the Weed Pokémon. Gloom gives off a very unpleasant smell. While strong against Water-type Pokémon, Gloom is weak against Fire and Flying types.

name: Vileplume
description: Vileplume, the Flower Pokémon. Using the largest flower petals in the world, it spreads large clouds of pollen that cause allergic reactions.

name: Paras
description: Paras, the Mushroom Pokémon. Rare mushrooms grow on its back.

name: Parasect
description: Parasect, the Mushroom Pokémon. It battles using poison spheres that spread from the mushroom canopy on its back.

name: Venonat
description: Venonat, a Bug Pokémon. Its eyes function as radar, allowing it to see in the dark.

name: Venomoth
description: Venomoth, an evolved form of Venonat. Tiny scales on its wings disperse various spores when they are flapped.

name: Diglett
description: Diglett. The movement of these Ground Pokémon can be easily detected by their tracks of upturned earth.

name: Dugtrio
description: Dugtrio, the evolved form of Diglett. No specific information available.

name: Meowth
description: Meowth, the Scratch Cat Pokémon. Meowth loves to roam at night to gather coins and other objects that sparkle, but it spends most of the daylight hours sleeping.

name: Persian
description: Persian, the Classy Cat Pokémon and the evolved form of Meowth. Persian can walk silently thanks to its nimble muscles. It pounces on its prey at lightning speed.

name: Psyduck
description: Psyduck, a Water Pokémon. Uses mysterious powers to perform various attacks. Psyduck constantly suffers from a headache.

name: Golduck
description: Golduck, the Duck Pokémon. The evolved form of Psyduck. Golduck is very adept at using its webbed hands and feet, making it the fastest swimming Pokémon of all.

name: Mankey
description: Mankey, a Pig Monkey Pokémon of the Fighting-type. Known for its superior footwork, it packs a powerful punch.

name: Primeape
description: Primeape. If you make eye contact with this evolved form of Mankey, it will chase you forever.

name: Growlithe
description: Growlithe, a Puppy Pokémon of pleasant demeanor and great diligence. It drives enemies away with barks and bites.

name: Arcanine
description: Arcanine, a Legendary Pokémon. The evolved form of Growlithe. Arcanine is known for its bravery and fierce loyalty. Growlithe evolves into Arcanine from its use of a Fire Stone.

name: Poliwag
description: Poliwag, the Tadpole Pokémon. It has no arms, but its tail makes it a strong swimmer.

name: Poliwhirl
description: Poliwhirl, the Tadpole Pokémon. Its highly developed muscles allow Poliwhirl to move efficiently on land, but it is even more agile in water.

name: Poliwrath
description: Poliwrath, the Tadpole Pokémon. Poliwrath is an excellent swimmer and its powerful muscles make its attacks extremely effective.

name: Abra
description: Abra, a Psychic Power Pokémon. It sleeps eighteen hours a day, but employs telekinesis even while sleeping.

name: Kadabra
description: Kadabra, a Psychic Pokémon. The evolved form of Abra. Employs powerful telekinetic attacks.

name: Alakazam
description: Alakazam, a Psi Pokémon. This Pokémon uses Psychic attacks to overcome its opponents.

name: Machop
description: Machop. Its body is pure muscle. Its special attack is the Seismic Toss.

name: Machoke
description: Machoke, the Superpower Pokémon. With enough strength to lift a giant truck with one hand, Machoke are often used for extremely heavy work.

name: Machamp
description: Machamp is a large, humanoid Pokémon with four well-muscled arms. Machamp punches extremely fast, throwing five hundred punches a second. With only one hand, it can move a mountain. Because of its four arms, it can hit from a multitude of angles and pin all of its foe's limbs at once.

name: Bellsprout
description: Bellsprout is a plant-based Pokémon with a stem-like brown body. This stem is long, thin and very flexible, making it capable of swerving rapidly to avoid many attacks or moving with blinding speed to capture prey. Its roots resemble feet, and it uses them as such.

name: Weepinbell
description: Weepinbell, the Flycatcher Pokémon. Weepinbell looks like a plant and covers opponents with a poisonous powder in order to catch them.

name: Victreebel
description: Victreebel has a bell-shaped body with a gaping mouth that has two sharp teeth. Covering Victreebel's mouth is a leaf with a long, brown, yellow-tipped vine growing out of it. The vine is flicked to mimic an animal in order to attract prey. Victreebel also produces a sweet scent to further aid in luring its victims. Acid that has dissolved numerous prey animals becomes sweeter and even more effective at attracting prey.

name: Tentacool
description: Tentacool, a Jellyfish Pokémon. 99% of its body is made up of water.

name: Tentacruel
description: Tentacruel, a Jellyfish Pokémon. An evolved form of the Tentacool. Its numerous tentacles serve as a powerful weapon. It is known as "The Gangster of the Sea."

name: Geodude
description: Geodude, the Rock Pokémon. Geodude has incredibly high defensive power, making it virtually resistant to any physical attacks.

name: Graveler
description: Graveler is a living, bipedal boulder. It has a rocky crest about its small eyes. Its preferred locomotion is rolling, specifically because it is a slow walker.

name: Golem
description: Golem, a Megaton Pokémon. Once a year it sheds its bedrock shell and grows larger.

name: Ponyta
description: Ponyta, a Fire Horse Pokémon. Its mane is made of intense flames.

name: Rapidash
description: Rapidash, the Fire Horse Pokémon. A Fire type. Rapidash loves to gallop. Whenever it sees something moving fast, it gets the urge to race.

name: Slowpoke
description: Slowpoke, the Dopey Pokémon. No one can tell what a Slowpoke is thinking, if it ever does think. Its specialty is fishing with its tail.

name: Slowbro
description: Slowbro, the Hermit Crab Pokémon. Slowbro are able to use powerful Psychic attacks, but generally prefers to avoid conflict.

name: Magnemite
description: Magnemite, a Magnet Pokémon. Its means of floating through the air are not understood. This very mysterious Pokémon is of the Electric type.

name: Magneton
description: Magneton, the Magnet Pokémon. The evolved form of Magnemite. Its anti-gravitational powers allow it to float, and it can emit powerful magnetic and electric fields.

name: Farfetch'd
description: Farfetch'd, a Wild Duck Pokémon. Farfetch'd makes a delicious meal, especially when cooked with leek. Because of this, Farfetch'd is nearly extinct.

name: Doduo
description: Doduo, the Twin Bird Pokémon. It runs faster than it can fly.

name: Dodrio
description: Dodrio, a three-headed Bird Pokémon that can run faster than it can fly. Its three heads represent joy, sorrow, and anger.

name: Seel
description: Seel is a pinniped Pokémon with a thick hide covered in bluish white fur. Preferring to sleep during the day, it hunts for prey under sheets of ice in the late day and evening hours. While it is a graceful swimmer, it is awkward and struggles to move on dry land.

name: Dewgong
description: Dewgong, the Sea Lion Pokémon. The evolved form of Seel. This Water/Ice Pokémon can easily resist extreme cold.

name: Grimer
description: Grimer, a Sludge Pokémon. Born from sludge, these Pokémon specialize in Sludge attacks.

name: Muk
description: Muk, Grimer's evolved form. Use extreme caution as its slimy form contains poison.

name: Shellder
description: Shellder is a black pearl-like Pokémon encased within a spiky, blue-violet bivalve shell. It has an enormously long red tongue, which it uses to burrow itself into sand and to lure and capture prey. Its body is known to be soft and tender; however, its shell is said to be harder than diamond.

name: Cloyster
description: Cloyster, a Bivalve Pokémon. Its shell is incredibly strong and resistant to a bomb. Its shell only opens when it attacks.

name: Gastly
description: Gastly, a Ghost Pokémon. It is usually invisible. Its specialty is Hypnosis.

name: Haunter
description: Haunter, the Gas Pokémon. After evolving from Gastly, this Haunter can learn the Dream Eater and Psychic attacks.

name: Gengar
description: Gengar, a Shadow Pokémon. The evolved form of Haunter. Details about this Pokémon are unknown.

name: Onix
description: Onix, the Rock Snake Pokémon. It tunnels through the ground which shakes when it raises its thunderous roar. It can move the ground at fifty miles per hour.

name: Drowzee
description: Drowzee. Said to be a descendant of the dream-eating tapir. It was the first Pokémon to use a combination attack like Hypnosis and Dream Eater.

name: Hypno
description: Hypno, a Hypnosis Pokémon. It carries a pendulum-like device and performs hypnotic attacks.

name: Krabby
description: Krabby. Lives near the shore. Its average height is about 16 inches.

name: Kingler
description: Kingler, the Pincer Pokémon. The evolved form of Krabby. Its crushing claws make it a powerful opponent.

name: Voltorb
description: Voltorb. The identity of this creature is unknown. It has an extreme personality, uses Electric attacks, and at times self-destructs.

name: Electrode
description: Electrode, the evolved form of Voltorb. Highly concentrated electric energy causes this Pokémon to explode unpredictably. Also known as "The Bomb Ball."

name: Exeggcute
description: Exeggcute, an Egg Pokémon. Although it resembles an egg, it is known to be more closely related to the seed of a plant.

name: Exeggutor
description: Exeggutor, a Coconut Pokémon. Also known as "The Walking Tropical Rain Forest." Each coconut has a distinct face and its own character. Its special attack is Hypnosis.

name: Cubone
description: A Ground-type Pokémon, Cubone. Cubone has earned its classification as the Lonely Pokémon from its usual attitude of caring only for itself.

name: Marowak
description: Marowak, a Bone Keeper Pokémon. Despite its small size, its offensive and defensive strength is impressive.

name: Hitmonlee
description: Hitmonlee, the Kicking Pokémon. This nimble Pokémon launches lethal kicks from almost any position.

name: Hitmonchan
description: Hitmonchan, a skilled Fighting Pokémon that packs an incredibly fast punch.

name: Lickitung
description: Lickitung, the Licking Pokémon. It uses a tongue that is more than twice the length of its body to battle, as well as to gather food.

name: Koffing
description: Koffing, the Poison Gas Pokémon. Koffing hovers in the air, thanks to the poisonous gases it contains, which have a foul odor and can explode.

name: Weezing
description: Weezing is a poisonous Pokemon with each head containing a different toxin. When its gases mix, Weezing becomes more toxic and putrid. Despite their stench and poison, its gases can be used to make top-grade perfume by diluting them to the highest level.

name: Rhyhorn
description: Rhyhorn, the Spikes Pokémon. It's covered in a tough armor, giving its Tackle attack an extraordinarily destructive power.

name: Rhydon
description: Rhydon, the evolved form of Rhyhorn. It is known as the Drill Pokémon. Its large horn gives it formidable attack power.

name: Chansey
description: Chansey, the Egg Pokémon, and the evolved form of Happiny. Chansey is a kind Pokémon who shares its egg with those who are sick or injured.

name: Tangela
description: Tangela, a Vine Pokémon. Its body is wrapped in vines. The rest of its form is hidden beneath these vines.

name: Kangaskhan
description: Kangaskhan, a Parent Pokémon. Once approaching extinction, they are now protected by law and inhabit the Safari Zone. Approach with extreme caution. The Kangaskhan is a rare Pokémon which raises its children in its pocket. They will attack viciously and without warning if they feel their young are threatened in any way.

name: Horsea
description: Horsea, a Dragon Pokémon. In this unique Pokémon species, thousands of Eggs hatch every spring, and then the male raises them himself.

name: Seadra
description: Seadra, a Dragon Pokémon. The evolved form of Horsea. Seadra has a violent temperament, and the quills that cover its body can render its victim unconscious.

name: Goldeen
description: Goldeen is a white, fish-like Pokémon with orange markings on its tail, back, and fins. It has a thin dorsal fin and long pectoral fins. It has a wild temperament, and will use its horn to smash its way to freedom if kept in an aquarium. Humans swimming near it must exercise caution lest Goldeen ram them.

name: Seaking
description: Seaking, the Goldfish Pokémon. Seaking is the evolved form of Goldeen. Its sharp, drill-like horn is capable of crushing even stone.

name: Staryu
description: Staryu. The core of this Water Pokémon shines in a rainbow of seven colors, a core that is valued by some as a type of jewelry.

name: Starmie
description: Starmie is a violet sea star-like Pokémon with a gold formation on its front. Starmie's jewel core, which can glow in seven colors, has developed to resemble a cut precious stone. The multi-color glowing of its core is also believed to be a method of communication inside the species.

name: Mr. Mime
description: Mr. Mime, the Barrier Pokémon. It uses pantomime to make actual walls appear. Because it is rarely discovered, information about this Pokémon is extremely limited.

name: Scyther
description: Scyther and Electabuzz are both rare Pokémon. They are able to distinguish colors and become enraged by the color red.

name: Jynx
description: Jynx, the Human Shape Pokémon. This Pokémon has some very unusual powers. Its special attack is the Lovely Kiss, which puts its opponent into a deep sleep.

name: Electabuzz
description: Electabuzz is a rare Pokémon. They are able to distinguish colors and become enraged by the color red.

name: Magmar
description: Magmar, the Spitfire Pokémon. Its body is like a furnace, making Magmar a living inferno. It has been discovered only near active volcanoes.

name: Pinsir
description: Pinsir. This fearsome Pokémon uses its powerful claws to put the squeeze on its opponents.

name: Tauros
description: Tauros, a Wild Bull Pokémon. When whipping itself with its three tails, its Tackle is a powerful destructive force.

name: Magikarp
description: Magikarp is a medium-sized fish Pokémon with large, heavy reddish-orange scales.

name: Gyarados
description: Gyarados. This Pokémon has a vicious temperament, so use extreme caution. Its fangs can crush stones and its scales are harder than steel.

name: Lapras
description: Lapras. This intellectually advanced Pokémon is able to understand human speech. With its mild temperament, Lapras prefers to carry humans on its back, rather than engage in Pokémon battles.

name: Ditto
description: Ditto, a Transform Pokémon. It is able to rearrange the cells of its body and assume any form. Its only attack is Transform.

name: Eevee
description: Eevee, the Evolution Pokémon. It has the potential to evolve into any one of three different Pokémon.

name: Vaporeon
description: Vaporeon, the Bubble Jet Pokémon. Vaporeon love fresh, clean water and can make their bodies melt away into water as well.

name: Jolteon
description: Jolteon, the Lightning Pokémon. When angered or frightened, the hairs on Jolteon's body become like needles that are fired at its opponents. It absorbs charged atoms and can produce 10,000 volts of electricity.

name: Flareon
description: Flareon, the Flame Pokémon. Flareon is the evolved form of Eevee. The air it inhales is ignited by a flame inside its body and expelled as fire.

name: Porygon
description: A Pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

name: Omanyte
description: Omanyte is believed these Pokémon became extinct tens of thousands of years ago. The details of their behavior is shrouded in mystery. Though some have speculated that they may still exist, none of these Pokémon have ever been seen alive.

name: Omastar
description: Omastar is believed these Pokémon became extinct tens of thousands of years ago. The details of their behavior is shrouded in mystery. Though some have speculated that they may still exist, none of these Pokémon have ever been seen alive.

name: Kabuto
description: Kabuto is believed these Pokémon became extinct tens of thousands of years ago. The details of their behavior is shrouded in mystery. Though some have speculated that they may still exist, none of these Pokémon have ever been seen alive.

name: Kabutops
description: Kabutops is believed these Pokémon became extinct tens of thousands of years ago. The details of their behavior is shrouded in mystery. Though some have speculated that they may still exist, none of these Pokémon have ever been seen alive.

name: Aerodactyl
description: Aerodactyl, an extinct Flying Pokémon. Its hard fangs suggest that it was a carnivore. Its sharp claws were probably used to capture prey.

name: Snorlax
description: Snorlax is the heaviest species of all known Pokémon, with some weighing more than 1,000 pounds.

name: Articuno
description: Articuno, the Freeze Pokémon. This Legendary Pokémon, with wings like thin sheets of ice, is believed to possess the ability to freeze water vapor and create snow.

name: Zapdos
description: Zapdos, the Electric Pokémon. Zapdos has both Electric and Flying elements and the flappage of its wings can create lightning.

name: Moltres
description: Moltres, a Legendary Pokémon. Its virtues symbolize the Pokémon League competitions.

name: Dratini
description: Dratini, the Dragon Pokémon. Dratini sheds its skin as it grows, often doing so while hidden behind large powerful waterfalls.

name: Dragonair
description: Dragonair, the Dragon Pokémon. A Legendary Pokémon that can freely make it rain or snow. It's said to be able to fly even though it doesn't have wings.

name: Dragonite
description: Dragonite, the Dragon Pokémon. This extremely rare and highly intelligent type is able to fly faster than any known Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo
description: Pokémon unknown. No available data.

name: Mew
description: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
